Human Resource Consultancy firm Virtual HR Services has partnernerd with a UK-based business support firm to launch a personal development tool targeting one million employees.The online tool, to be introduced at the end of the month, aims to reach 10,000 companies in the next three years. It has been adopted by 20 local companies.Virtual HR managing director Gladys Ogallo said the tool will help provide a backup for academic testimonials that employees and recruits present for hiring. The testing tool shows a person s suitability to a role that they are presently in, and their prospects for future roles, thus initiating need for growth, Ogallo said in a statement.Co-operative Bank of Kenya, Britam, ICEA Lion Group, Chase Bank Kenya, Capwell Industries, Strathmore Business School and ACORN Management Services are using the tool.